<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-01-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="207" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d207">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">760d.61/31</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Finnish Minister</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Saastamoinen</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#left">No. 12</seg></opener>
                            <p>The Envoy Extraordinary and Minister Plenipotentiary of Finland
                                presents his compliments to the Acting Secretary of State and
                                respectfully begs to advise that the treaty of peace between Finland
                                and Russia became effective at 6:25 p.m. December 31, 1920.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <dateline rendition="#left">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-01-04"><hi rend="italic">January 4, 1921</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>